# Principle of Least Exposure

- Default every declaration to `internal` unless an external consumer must reference it by name.
- Promote to `public` only when a consumer outside the module explicitly needs it.
- It is easy to make something public later; making something internal is a breaking change.
- Implementation classes, storage backends, internal interfaces between components, and factory plumbing should always be `internal`.
- When in doubt, start `internal` and open it up when the need arises.
